    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A narrative, top-down structure was designed to guide a user (e.g., a recruiter) through a logical story. It starts with a high-level summary (Who is he?), moves to a visual timeline (What has he done?), dives into a detailed analysis of his transferable skills (Why does his experience matter?), visualizes his capabilities (What can he do?), and concludes with his strategic value (Why is he a good fit for modern HR?). This structure is more persuasive and easier to digest than a standard resume format. Interactive tabs are used in the deep-dive section to manage detailed content without creating an overwhelmingly long page, allowing for user-driven exploration. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Key Stats -> Goal: Inform -> Method: Large numbers in styled cards. Interaction: None. Justification: Provides a quick, scannable overview of key achievements.
        - Experience Timeline -> Goal: Change -> Method: Vertical timeline using HTML/CSS. Interaction: None. Justification: Clearly shows the concurrent nature of his academic and professional pursuits, highlighting his proactivity. NO SVG/Mermaid used.
        - Transferable Skills -> Goal: Organize/Relationships -> Method: Interactive Tabs. Interaction: User clicks to switch between experiences. Justification: Organizes detailed analysis cleanly, allowing users to focus on one area at a time while explicitly connecting past actions to future HR value.
        - Skills Breakdown -> Goal: Compare -> Method: Radar Chart (Chart.js/Canvas). Interaction: Tooltips on hover. Justification: A radar chart effectively visualizes the balance and breadth across different skill categories (Soft, Technical, HR), showcasing him as a well-rounded candidate.
        - Strategic Fit -> Goal: Inform -> Method: Styled text blocks with icons (Unicode). Interaction: None. Justification: Concludes the narrative with a strong, clear summary of his unique value proposition for a forward-thinking company.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
